HEADWORD: Pseudovum
<hw>Pseu*do"vum</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Pseudova</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[NL. See <er>Pseudo-</er>,
and <er>Ovum</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>An egglike germ
produced by the agamic females of some insects and other animals, and by
the larv⟦ae⟧ of certain insects. It is capable of development without
fertilization. See <xex>Illust.</xex> of
<er>P⟦ae⟧dogenesis</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

